(firstQuint)Paclitaxel Releasing Balloon in Patients Presenting With In-Stent Restenosis.

 All patients are treated with the paclitaxel releasing balloon Pantera Lux.

 The indication is in-stent restenosis in either bare metal stent (BMS) or drug eluting stent (DES).

 Clinical follow up visits at 1, 6 and 12 months.

 Angiographic follow up visit at 6 months.

